The paper focuses on developing robot perception systems for recognizing objects in real-world settings, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper specifically discusses the use of computer vision algorithms for object recognition, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the need for large quantities of ground truth data, which could involve machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper presents a tool for acquiring high quality ground truth annotation, which could involve machine learning and deep learning techniques (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the creation of a dataset, which could involve multimedia (cs.MM) as well.
